<a href="#0" id="0">In bringing in extra-linguistic information to learn word representations, our work falls into the general domain of multimodal learning; while other work has used visual information to improve distributed representations [] , this work generally exploits information about the object being described (e.g.,, strawberry and a picture of a strawberry); in contrast, we use information about the speaker to learn representations that vary according to contextual variables from the speaker ’ s perspective.</a>
